  "text": "The Donnan potential is interpreted physically as the change in electrostatic potential across the reservoir-suspension interface, and mathematically as a Lagrange multiplier for the constraint of global electroneutrality. Combining the Poisson equation for the potential [Eq. (12)] with the Boltzmann approximation for the microion densities [Eq. [CITATION_1] or (20)], the Poisson-Boltzmann equation becomes",
